API Documentation
Base URL: http://localhost:8080/api/v1

Swagger UI: http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html

POST
/orders
Create Order
Creates a new order with multiple items.

Request Body:
{
  "customerName": "John Doe",
  "customerEmail": "john.doe@example.com",
  "orderItems": [
    {
      "productId": 101,
      "productName": "Laptop",
      "quantity": 1,
      "price": 1299.99
    },
    {
      "productId": 102,
      "productName": "Mouse",
      "quantity": 2,
      "price": 29.99
    }
  ]
}
Response (201 Created):
{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Order created successfully",
  "data": {
    "id": 1,
    "orderNumber": "ORD-20251107-00001",
    "customerName": "John Doe",
    "customerEmail": "john.doe@example.com",
    "status": "PENDING",
    "totalAmount": 1359.97,
    "orderItems": [...],
    "createdAt": "2025-11-07T23:00:00",
    "updatedAt": "2025-11-07T23:00:00"
  },
  "timestamp": "2025-11-07T23:00:00"
}
GET
/orders/{id}
Get Order by ID
Retrieves order details by order ID.

Path Parameters:
id (Long) - Order ID
Response (200 OK):
{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Order retrieved successfully",
  "data": { /* Order details */ },
  "timestamp": "2025-11-07T23:00:00"
}
Error Response (404 Not Found):
{
  "timestamp": "2025-11-07T23:00:00",
  "status": 404,
  "error": "Not Found",
  "message": "Order not found with id: 999",
  "details": []
}
GET
/orders
List All Orders
Retrieves all orders with pagination and optional status filter.

Query Parameters:
status (Optional) - Filter by order status (PENDING, PROCESSING, SHIPPED, DELIVERED)
page (Optional, default: 0) - Page number
size (Optional, default: 10) - Page size
sort (Optional, default: createdAt,desc) - Sort criteria
Example: GET /orders?status=PENDING&page=0&size=20
PATCH
/orders/{id}/status
Update Order Status
Updates the status of an existing order.

Request Body:
{
  "status": "PROCESSING"
}
Valid Status Transitions:
PENDING → PROCESSING
PROCESSING → SHIPPED
SHIPPED → DELIVERED
DELETE
/orders/{id}
Cancel Order
Cancels an order. Only PENDING orders can be cancelled.

Response (200 OK):
{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Order cancelled successfully",
  "data": null,
  "timestamp": "2025-11-07T23:00:00"
}
Error Response (400 Bad Request):
{
  "timestamp": "2025-11-07T23:00:00",
  "status": 400,
  "error": "Bad Request",
  "message": "Cannot cancel order. Only PENDING orders can be cancelled",
  "details": []
}